description.narrative: By the end of 2018, national capacities are strengthened to improve the PNDS planning, budgeting and monitoring system and to better take into account equity in programs, which contributes to Child Health, Health Systems Strengthening, Policy, Guidance And Technical Support For Country Programming And Reporting. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2018, at least 80% of mothers and children, especially the most vulnerable, use the comprehensive integrated package of quality interventions for maternal, newborn and child health.
